cameraOffset.title: Camera Offset
cameraOffset.description: The distance and angle the camera will follow the car. Game needs to be reloaded for settings to take full effect!

lerpAmount.title: Lerp Amount
lerpAmount.description: The amount to lerp the camera towards its desired position every frame based on a 60fps frame rate. Lerping is frame rate independent though and will be correct for other frame rates.

postTrackingOffset.title: Post Tracking Offset
postTrackingOffset.description: The local space offset applied after all other tracking logic runs

targetFollowEntity.title: Target Follow Entity
targetFollowEntity.description: The invisible entity following the target, increases smoothness

followsAmmoVehicle.description: If true, this will place a 3-frame delay before moving to follow a target

durability.description: Range between -10 and +10 that scales damage dealt upon collision. Higher means stronger.

driftiness.description: Range between 0 and 1 describing how likely the car will lose traction cornering. 0 will have no traction, 1 will never lose traction.

driftTraction.description: Range between 0 and 10 that applies when the rear tires slip. 0 will slide a lot, 10 will not slide.

renderEntity.title: Render Entity
renderEntity.description: The visible entity containing the wheel's 3D model

disabledEntityPosition.description: Position entities are teleported to when not in use.

maxVehicleLimit.description: The highest number of vehicles that will be spawned on high-end devices

npcVehicleMaterials.description: These will occupy the variable color space on the vehicle renders

mainTextureMaterial.description: The main texture palette used by all vehicle renders

supportsSpawns.description: Can vehicles spawn at this waypoint? Disable if waypoint is inside intersection

hand.description: hand.R or .L entity from the Armature.

supportsSpawns.description: Can pedestrians spawn at this waypoint?

disabledEntityPosition.description: Position entities are teleported to when not in use.

maxPedLimit.description: The highest number of peds that will be spawned on high-end devices

renderElement.description: Element to render the texture to

useWindowSize.description: Render output matches browser window dimensions

mapSize.description: Width and depth of the map. Used to calculate grid cell dimensions.

gridSize.description: Number of cells both width and depth. Grids are always 2D squares.

hostWaypoint.description: NPC waypoint this targets is a child of

graceTimeS.description: Time in seconds to unlock extra job time before job:failed fires.

dependants.description: These region buttons have to be unlocked first before this one is unlocked

returnToDrive.description: Page returns to driving state instead of home screen

postFollowTranslation.description: The position translation applied after we've copied the position and rotation.

schema.name: displayPosition
schema.description: Adjusts the showroom/homescreen position to accommodate all ride heights

resetEvent.description: Event that resets the count when fired

increaseEvent.description: Event that increases the count when fired

hideEvents.description: Event that hides the badge when fired

showEvents.description: Event that shows the badge when fired

disableOnFinish.description: Entity will set enabled to false when animation is complete.

staticOpacity.description: Script will not modify opacity (useful for button hover states).

fadeInEvent.description: Fade in will start as soon as this event is fired upon the entity

fadeInCurve.description: Shape of the fade in curve

fadeDuration.description: Duration in seconds to fade the audio in

bounceStartOffset.description: How far through the animation do we start between 0.0 and 1.0
